Thu Feb 24 14:11:58 CET 2000 Erik Corry
   * Assume when execing that FD_CLOEXEC flag is set on fd's and clear it on
     those fds we want to keep open across an exec (new program start)
   * Clear the nonblock flag on fds we keep open in order not to confuse
     subprograms that expect blocking IO
Wed Jan 12 17:21:54 CET 2000 Erik Corry
   * Fixed obscure bug in fd handling on fork.

RELEASE 4.2:
============

Added dlfcn.bet with support for dynamic linking of shared object
files.

VERSION 1.4
=============
With v1.4 the following changes were introduced:

All files:
==========

1) INCLUDE fragments have been replaced by INCLUDE properties.

2) Fragment *group* syntax ( [[ and ]] ) has been removed

errorscreen.bet:
================

1) New file containing pattern corresponding to the standard error
   stream (errorscreen)

iostate.bet:
============

1) New file containing interface to UNIX file descriptors.
   Used with systemenv.
